WEBVTT

00:02:58.603 --> 00:03:00.813
sharing many intellectual interests,

00:03:00.813 --> 00:03:02.123
hosting and debating

00:03:02.123 --> 00:03:04.543
the leading scholars of the day.

00:03:04.543 --> 00:03:07.673
Meanwhile, Alexios’s military excursions

00:03:07.673 --> 00:03:09.063
began to pay off,

00:03:09.063 --> 00:03:10.893
restoring many of the empire’s

00:03:10.893 --> 00:03:12.573
former territories.

00:03:12.573 --> 00:03:13.983
As her father aged,

00:03:13.983 --> 00:03:16.353
Anna and her husband helped her parents

00:03:16.353 --> 00:03:18.423
with their imperial duties.

00:03:18.423 --> 00:03:19.573
During this time,

00:03:19.573 --> 00:03:21.163
Anna reportedly advocated for

00:03:21.163 --> 00:03:22.813
just treatment of the people

00:03:22.813 --> 00:03:25.233
in their disputes with the government.

00:03:25.233 --> 00:03:27.273
After Alexios’s death,

00:03:27.273 --> 00:03:29.673
Anna’s brother John ascended to the throne

00:03:29.673 --> 00:03:30.923
and Anna turned back